headline: United Airlines Scores Relative Strength Rating Upgrade; Hits Key Threshold
summary: On Wednesday, shares of United Airlines jumped nearly 4% in midday trading.  UAL is very close to an all-time high and could top it as early as today as the airlines sector perks up.  Its gains come on the heels of a lift for Southwest Airlines, which shot up 18.7% on Jan. 29 after that carrier reported outstanding earnings results.
